                  </hi>. I live in Bucklersbury. On the 12th of July I was in Wormwood-street, between one and two o'clock, with William Fryer, I saw the two prisoners behind us—I turned round and saw something pass between them—I said to Fryer, "Your pocket is picked"—he fol<lb></lb>lowed Hardwidge, and I followed Thompson.</p>
